t2ede_q_42: Last year at this time (Aug '18), I was very sick and just beginning to receive treatment. I exercised excessively, constantly weighed myself, and purged multiple times a day. I was always thinking about food and losing weight. I isolated myself from school and relationships, spending most of my time alone in my room. This was both intentional and inadvertent; I would decline social invitations because of food, and then I was too exhausted to do much of anything. Over the following several months, I stepped up and down from various levels of treatment. I am proud to say I am doing very well right now! I honestly don't know how I got better, but I sure had a lot of help along the way. And for that, I am thankful.
